Agile Workflow and Work Breakdown Structure

1. Product Vision & Backlog Definition
   1.1. Define core product goals and scope
       - Clarify product outcome: online exam system with behavior monitoring and reporting
       - Confirm user roles: examiner/admin, examinee
       - Decide deployment target: PostgreSQL production, SQLite dev fallback
       - Establish non-functional goals: responsive UI, real-time feedback, data integrity
   1.2. Capture project requirements from documentation
       - Map backend responsibilities to feature areas: auth, exams, session, monitoring, behavior, reports, profile
       - Map frontend modules to pages and components: auth, dashboard, exams, session, monitoring, reports, profile
       - Align schema design with API and feature needs: users, exams, questions, sessions, logs, alerts
       - Confirm monitoring flow: webcam capture → WebSocket/REST delivery → AI processing → alerts
   1.3. Create product backlog items (epics and stories)
       - Epic: Authentication & User Management
           * Story: Implement registration API and frontend form
           * Story: Implement login and JWT/session handling
           * Story: Build role-aware protected routes
           * Story: Add profile retrieval and update flows
       - Epic: Exam Management
           * Story: Create exam CRUD backend APIs
           * Story: Add question CRUD and options storage
           * Story: Build examiner exam list and exam detail views
           * Story: Add exam publish/archive actions
       - Epic: Session & Responses
           * Story: Start session endpoint and session record creation
           * Story: Implement timer and time remaining persistence
           * Story: Capture answer submission per question
           * Story: End session, calculate score, and save results
       - Epic: Monitoring & Real-Time Communication
           * Story: Build WebSocket consumer for frame streaming
           * Story: Add REST /api/monitoring/frame fallback endpoint
           * Story: Create frontend webcam streamer and monitoring panel
           * Story: Emit analysis results and alerts in real time
       - Epic: Behavior Analysis & Alerts
           * Story: Model behavior log structure and storage
           * Story: Create scoring service for suspicious behavior
           * Story: Generate alert records and severity levels
           * Story: Build UI indicators for detected behaviors
       - Epic: Reporting & Analytics
           * Story: Implement report service and session log retrieval
           * Story: Build report viewer and filter interfaces
           * Story: Add export option for CSV/PDF
           * Story: Show recent alerts and session summaries
       - Epic: Shared Architecture & Utilities
           * Story: Create base repository/service classes
           * Story: Add DTOs, validators, timestamp mixins
           * Story: Build shared UI layout components and loading/error screens
           * Story: Configure API base URL and environment constants

2. Agile Iterations (Sprints)
   2.1. Sprint 1: Foundation & Core Platform
       - Task 2.1.1: Initialize backend project structure and install requirements
       - Task 2.1.2: Create Django settings modules and environment config
       - Task 2.1.3: Configure URL routing, ASGI, WSGI, and channels settings
       - Task 2.1.4: Implement core shared utilities and helpers
       - Task 2.1.5: Bootstrap frontend with Vite and install React dependencies
       - Task 2.1.6: Add router, protected routes, auth provider, query provider
       - Task 2.1.7: Build site shell: header, sidebar, footer, loading, error states
       - Task 2.1.8: Implement auth backend models and login/register endpoints
       - Task 2.1.9: Add frontend login/register pages and state management
   2.2. Sprint 2: Exam Management & Session Engine
       - Task 2.2.1: Build exam models, migrations, and repository methods
       - Task 2.2.2: Implement exam serializers, API views, and URL routes
       - Task 2.2.3: Add question model, options JSON storage, and link to exams
       - Task 2.2.4: Create exam CRUD endpoints and question management APIs
       - Task 2.2.5: Implement session model, start/terminate endpoints, and logs
       - Task 2.2.6: Add response model, answer persistence, and scoring fields
       - Task 2.2.7: Build examinee exam page, timer component, and answer sheet UI
       - Task 2.2.8: Create examiner exam management page and exam detail view
   2.3. Sprint 3: Monitoring & Real-Time Communication
       - Task 2.3.1: Add monitoring feature service and frame processing action
       - Task 2.3.2: Build Django Channels consumer and websocket routing
       - Task 2.3.3: Add REST fallback `/api/monitoring/frame/` endpoint
       - Task 2.3.4: Implement frontend webcam capture hook and stream client
       - Task 2.3.5: Build monitoring dashboard, webcam tile, and alert badge
       - Task 2.3.6: Wire websocket events for frame_stream and analysis_result
       - Task 2.3.7: Create alert handling and live grid behavior updates
   2.4. Sprint 4: Behavior Analysis & Reporting
       - Task 2.4.1: Define behavior log schema and persistence layer
       - Task 2.4.2: Implement scoring service and behavior evaluation action
       - Task 2.4.3: Add alert generation on suspicious event thresholds
       - Task 2.4.4: Build report service endpoints and session analytics APIs
       - Task 2.4.5: Create frontend behavior log list and score indicator components
       - Task 2.4.6: Build report table, session log viewer, and export button
       - Task 2.4.7: Add reports page and examiner analytics dashboard
   2.5. Sprint 5: Polish, Data, and Deployment Readiness
       - Task 2.5.1: Implement profile management and avatar upload flows
       - Task 2.5.2: Add examiner/examinee dashboards and overview cards
       - Task 2.5.3: Add responsive layout fixes and accessibility improvements
       - Task 2.5.4: Generate seed data and verify SQLite workflow
       - Task 2.5.5: Run end-to-end API and monitoring integration tests
       - Task 2.5.6: Finalize production settings, CORS, static/media config
       - Task 2.5.7: Document setup, run, and deployment instructions

3. Work Breakdown Structure (WBS)
   3.1. Project Initiation
       - Task 3.1.1: Review `Project.json`, API design, backend and frontend structure docs
       - Task 3.1.2: Create a detailed backlog from epics and user stories
       - Task 3.1.3: Define acceptance criteria for each sprint
       - Task 3.1.4: Establish definitions of done and test coverage goals
   3.2. Backend Architecture
       3.2.1. Core
           - Task 3.2.1.1: Configure Django settings and environment file handling
           - Task 3.2.1.2: Build URL and route management for API and websocket paths
           - Task 3.2.1.3: Add global exception handlers and permission utilities
           - Task 3.2.1.4: Implement request/response helpers and API response formatting
       3.2.2. Shared
           - Task 3.2.2.1: Create `base_repository` and `base_service` abstractions
           - Task 3.2.2.2: Add DTO base classes and shared validation routines
           - Task 3.2.2.3: Implement timestamp mixin and reusable model mixins
           - Task 3.2.2.4: Add shared utility functions for formatting and business logic
       3.2.3. Features
           - Task 3.2.3.1: Auth feature: user repository, auth service, JWT/session actions, user endpoints
           - Task 3.2.3.2: Exams feature: exam/question models, CRUD services, publish/archive actions, serializers
           - Task 3.2.3.3: Session feature: lifecycle actions, answer submission, status updates, logs
           - Task 3.2.3.4: Monitoring feature: frame service, websocket consumer, REST fallback, API view
           - Task 3.2.3.5: Behavior feature: scoring engine, behavior repository, evaluation actions
           - Task 3.2.3.6: Reports feature: report generation, filtering, summary export
           - Task 3.2.3.7: Profile feature: user profile APIs and update actions
       3.2.4. AI Module
           - Task 3.2.4.1: Define AI pipeline entry points and config contracts
           - Task 3.2.4.2: Add preprocessing utilities for frame normalization
           - Task 3.2.4.3: Integrate detection/recognition modules with monitoring flow
           - Task 3.2.4.4: Produce structured analysis output for behavior service consumption
   3.3. Frontend Architecture
       3.3.1. Core Layer
           - Task 3.3.1.1: Configure router with public and role-protected routes
           - Task 3.3.1.2: Implement authentication provider and session persistence
           - Task 3.3.1.3: Add WebSocket provider and event dispatch hooks
           - Task 3.3.1.4: Build theme provider and environment-based API client
       3.3.2. Feature Modules
           - Task 3.3.2.1: Auth: login/register form components, validation, API hooks
           - Task 3.3.2.2: Exams: exam builder UI, question editor, exam list view
           - Task 3.3.2.3: Session: timer hook, answer sheet, question navigation, auto-save
           - Task 3.3.2.4: Monitoring: webcam stream hook, monitoring panel, alert badge
           - Task 3.3.2.5: Behavior: score indicator, flag list, behavior log view
           - Task 3.3.2.6: Dashboard: overview cards, recent alerts, stats chart
           - Task 3.3.2.7: Reports: report table, export button, log viewer components
           - Task 3.3.2.8: Profile: profile form and avatar upload workflow
       3.3.3. Shared Layer
           - Task 3.3.3.1: Create reusable UI components and layout shell
           - Task 3.3.3.2: Build loading, error, and empty-state components
           - Task 3.3.3.3: Implement shared hooks for debounce, local storage, and API helpers
           - Task 3.3.3.4: Define global types and shared utility functions
   3.4. Database Design
       - Task 3.4.1: Create schema for users, exams, questions, sessions, responses
       - Task 3.4.2: Add session logs, behavior logs, alerts tables
       - Task 3.4.3: Define foreign key relationships and cascade rules
       - Task 3.4.4: Add indexes for common query patterns on users, exams, sessions
       - Task 3.4.5: Validate SQLite dev schema compatibility with PostgreSQL target
   3.5. Quality & Validation
       - Task 3.5.1: Write backend tests for auth, exams, session, monitoring, behavior, reports
       - Task 3.5.2: Add frontend tests for forms, hooks, and page flows
       - Task 3.5.3: Build integration tests for `/api/monitoring/frame/`, websocket events, and session flows
       - Task 3.5.4: Create seed data scripts and verify data import/export
       - Task 3.5.5: Conduct acceptance checks for user story completion and bug fixes

4. Release Planning
   4.1. MVP Release
       - Task 4.1.1: Deliver login/register, user profile, auth-protected routes
       - Task 4.1.2: Deliver exam CRUD, question management, and start/submit session flows
       - Task 4.1.3: Deliver monitoring panel with webcam stream and fallback frame upload
       - Task 4.1.4: Deliver basic reporting, recent alerts, and session summary pages
       - Task 4.1.5: Ensure SQLite development flow and seed data support
   4.2. Post-MVP Enhancements
       - Task 4.2.1: Improve AI behavior detection and alert accuracy
       - Task 4.2.2: Add posture/gaze/object detection event types
       - Task 4.2.3: Expand report exports and admin dashboard analytics
       - Task 4.2.4: Improve UX polish, accessibility, and responsive UI
       - Task 4.2.5: Plan PostgreSQL migration and production deployment

5. Continuous Improvement
   - Task 5.1: Review sprint results and update backlog every iteration
   - Task 5.2: Refine user stories with acceptance criteria and dependencies
   - Task 5.3: Track cross-team integration between backend, frontend, AI, and database
   - Task 5.4: Maintain documentation for architecture, API, setup, and deployment

